what-it-does: Checks for an empty type-checking block.
why-is-this-bad:
The type-checking block does not do anything and should be removed to avoid
confusion.
example:
from typing import TYPE_CHECKING

if TYPE_CHECKING:
    pass

print("Hello, world!")



Use instead:


print("Hello, world!")

example-split.example-before:
from typing import TYPE_CHECKING

if TYPE_CHECKING:
    pass

print("Hello, world!")
